The team was named during the one-day trials on Monday at the Moi International Sports Centre, Kasarani.
KNPC president Agnes Aluoch disclosed that they have already written to the Ministry of Sports regarding funding, noting that the Sh26 million will be used towards the team’s 10-day camp before departure, accommodation and allowances.
“We also require to purchase one T54 special wheelchair for racing and some competition kit, especially the spikes,” said Aluoch, adding that she is confident the government will respond positively to their financial request.



