Despite taking a team of nine athletes, Kenya still claimed six medals; three gold, one silver and two bronze during the 2016 Rio Paralympic Games.
The team:
Men:
Wilson Bii (T11) 1,500m, 5,000m; Samwel Muchai (T11) 1,500m, 5,000m; Rodgers Kiprop (T11) 5,000m; Eric Sang (T11) 1,500m; John Torotich (T12) 1,500m, 5,000m; Bernard Koskei (T12) 1,500m, 5,000m; Henry Kirwa (T12) 1,500m, 5,000m; Samson Ojuka (T37) 100m, 200m, long jump; Gilbert Lagat (T12) 400m; Henry Nzungi (T12) 100m, Long jump; Wesley Sang (T46) 1,500m, Stanley Misik (T46) 1,500m); Felix Kipruto (T46) 1,500m; Daniel Safari (F42) high jump; James Magerere (F57)  shotput, javelin; James Mugo (F57) shotput, javelin; Vincent Mutai (T46) 100m, long jump; Wilfred Laisikwa (T37) 200m, 400m; Ronald Yego (T37) 200m, 400m; Joseph Kamau (T37) 200m, 400m; Rajab Chetty (F11) shotput; Augustino Kilonzo (F11) shotput; John Njoroge (T11) 400m; John Wambua (T54), 100, 200m, 400m; Samson Njoroge (F57) shotput, javelin; Joseph Kyaka (T 37) 1,500m.
Women:
Nancy Koech (T11) 400m, 1,500m; Mary Waithera (T11) 400m, 1,500m; Nelly Nasimiyu (T12) 400m, 1,500m; Hannah Ngendo (T12) 400m, 1,500m; Irene Tanui (T46) 200m, 400m; Sylvia Olero (F44) discus; Nelly Sile (F56) shotput, javelin; Margaret Njeri (F57) shotput, discus; Jennifer Chepkoech(f40) shotput; Linet Ogwal (F57) shotput, discus; Caroline Wanjira (T54) 100m, 200m, 400m.Guides: Robert Tarus, James Boit, Alpha Malinga, David Korir, Musa Muiruri, Kelly Otinya, Damaris Nzisa, Charles Macharia, Albanus Mutuku, Stephen Waweru.



